==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coss
<hw>Coss</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Pers.
<ets>k⟦omac⟧s</ets> a road measure of about two miles; or Skr.
<ets>kr⟦omac⟧⟦cced⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Hindoo measure of distance,
varying from one and a half to two English miles.</def>
<rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Coss
<hw>Coss</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>cosa</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
thing (only in phrase below).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rule of Coss</b></col>, <cd>an old name for
<xex>Algebra</xex>. <ety>[It. <xex>regola di cosa</xex> rule of thing,
the unknown quantity being called the <xex>cosa</xex>, or the
thing.]</ety></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cossack</ent>⟦br⟧
